1 B. Upon securing federal funding, the The Bureau shall create
2 an Office of Liaison for Missing and Murdered Indigenous Persons.
3 Any individual hired within the Office shall have significant
4 experience working with tribal communities. Subject to available
5 funding, the Office shall include a missing persons specialist.
6 C. The Office of Liaison for Missing and Murdered Indigenous
7 Persons shall:
8 1. Work with state, tribal and federal law enforcement agencies
9 on missing persons and homicide cases involving American Indian
10 individuals;
11 2. Develop a best practices protocol for law enforcement
12 response to missing persons reports involving American Indian
13 individuals;
14 3. Assist families, tribal agencies and nongovernmental
15 entities in using the National Missing and Unidentified Persons
16 System (NamUs) and other resources;
17 4. Provide guidance to victims' families with navigating state
18 and federal district court cases;
19 5. Coordinate with other state offices including, but not
20 limited to, the Office of the Chief Medical Examiner, agency tribal
21 liaisons and the Secretary of Native American Affairs to develop
22 training and education on missing and murdered indigenous persons
23 issues and the state-tribal government-to-government relationship;
